      "category": "Style",
      "description": "In dense formal passages, one or two sentences of plain, direct language restate what the formalism *means* \u2014 not what it specifies \u2014 strengthening the reader's trust that the author commands the machinery. These moments are brief (one sentence), arrive only after the formal specification they restate, and return immediately to formal register. The contrast is what makes them effective.",
