          "label": "The plain restatement articulates what the formalism means or implies, not what it technically specifies"
        },
        {
          "id": "immediate_return",
          "label": "Formal register resumes immediately after the plain-language moment without lingering or expanding the aside"
        },
        {
          "id": "strategic_placement",
          "label": "Plain-language moments are placed at points of maximum density or conceptual payoff, not distributed uniformly"
        }
      ],
      "priority": 3
    },
    {
      "name": "Formalism in Service of Argument",
      "category": "Content",
      "description": "Formal definitions, notation, and technical machinery are introduced in direct response to a stated problem and are explicitly connected to their argumentative purpose. The formalism resolves or sharpens a question the surrounding prose has raised; it is never self-standing or presented as its own justification.",
      "dimensions": [
        {
          "id": "formalism_motivated",
          "label": "Each piece of formal notation or machinery is introduced in response to a named problem, not presented self-standingly"
        },
        {
          "id": "formalism_cashed_out",
          "label": "Formal results or definitions are connected back to what they mean for the argument or design"
        },
        {
          "id": "claims_grounded",
          "label": "Empirical or behavioral claims that underpin the formalism are flagged for evidential grounding (e.g., citation placeholders)"
        },
        {
          "id": "notation_earns_place",
          "label": "Notation and formal apparatus sharpen or resolve a question rather than restating in symbols what prose already said"
        }
      ],
      "priority": 4
    },
    {
      "name": "Formal Register and Precision",
      "category": "Style",
      "description": "Language is precise and academic throughout, with no casual phrasing, colloquialisms, or unnecessary hedging. Terminology is consistent across sections. Register shifts are controlled, deliberate, and visibly marked (e.g., 'put simply'), never accidental or gradual.",
      "dimensions": [
        {
          "id": "no_casual_phrasing",
          "label": "No colloquialisms, casual transitions, or informal vocabulary appear outside of marked plain-language moments"
        },
        {
          "id": "terminological_consistency",
          "label": "Technical terms and names for concepts are used consistently across all sections"
        },
        {
          "id": "register_shifts_marked",
          "label": "Any departure from formal register is explicitly signaled (e.g., 'put plainly,' 'put simply') and visibly intentional"
        },
        {
          "id": "precise_vocabulary",
          "label": "Word choices are specific and exact, avoiding vague or generic academic filler (e.g., 'clear and effective')"
        }
      ],
      "priority": 5
    }
  ],
  "version": 2,
  "source": "criteria_classification",
  "writing_type": "formal academic research papers",
  "user_goals_summary": "This user writes dense, formally rigorous academic prose and cares most about argumentative architecture: every section must earn its place by naming the problem it responds to and cashing out what its machinery gains. Formalism is valued highly but treated as a means to argumentative ends, not an end in itself. The user expects formal register throughout, with rare, disciplined moments of plain-language directness that strengthen rather than undermine the reader's trust in the technical apparatus.",
  "coaching_notes": "This user diagnoses structural issues with exceptional precision \u2014 they identify the exact sentence where an argument falters and articulate the principle it violates. They value logical dependency above all: every piece of writing must feel like a chain of forced consequences, not a sequence of independent choices. When giving feedback, they consistently frame issues as 'the implicit thing that needs to be made explicit,' so surfacing latent logical connections is the single highest-leverage move. They accept formalism readily and never ask for simplification, but they will push back hard if formalism is not in service of an argumentative claim."
}

RECENT CONVERSATION CONTEXT (shows the user's writing preferences and interactions):
cause $\psi_t$ guides rather than constrains generation, it cannot prevent the system from producing outputs that violate preference dimensions on which confidence is already high. Hard filtering closes this gap by applying post-hoc constraints derived from high-confidence preference estimates to candidate outputs before presentation to $\mathcal{U}$. Outputs that violate constraints along dimensions where $\sigma_j^2$ falls below a predefined confidence threshold $\epsilon$ are regenerated, ensuring that the system does not repeatedly expose $\mathcal{U}$ to violations of well-established preference patterns.

Put simply: soft conditioning lets the system act on hunches without committing to them, while hard filtering ensures it never repeats a mistake it has already learned to recognize. Together, they allow the system to behave usefully from the very first interaction, when $\hat{P}_t$ is diffuse, through to late-stage interactions when it has substantially converged — without requiring a separate reconfiguration of the pipeline at any intermediate point.

</draft>

The hard filtering paragraph now opens by naming the specific gap that soft conditioning leaves open — the inability to enforce constraints on already-settled dimensions — before specifying how filtering addresses it. The two mechanisms are no longer parallel options but a logical sequence in which the second is necessitated by a structural property of the first.

[Message #18 — user]
This is landing. The dependency chain from the opening through soft conditioning into hard filtering is exactly right — the hard filtering paragraph now reads as the necessary consequence of a specific limitation rather than the second item in a list, and that distinction matters. The 'put simply' moment is doing precisely what it should: one sentence, then back to register, no overstay. I'd accept this as is. If you wanted one final polish pass, the only thing I'd look at is whether the cite-aware scaffolding has enough room — a couple of the stronger empirical claims (particularly around the behavioral justification for soft conditioning) might benefit from a bracketed placeholder for a reference, just to signal to reviewers that the claim is grounded. But that's a light editorial note, not a structural concern. The passage is working.

